    "summary": "Devoted young architect with a persistent motivation to use his research and design skills to change the living environment of people for the better. Design projects with a strong focus on the scale level that is at the interface between architectural and urban design have my special interest. Currently I am mostly working within Dutch contexts on these scale levels at KCAP in Rotterdam.\nI have notable field experience within the international urban development practice in Venezuela (Car\u00e1cas) and Colombia (Medell\u00edn). With regards to these contexts I am especially interested in slum upgrading projects and urban strategies aiming at inclusive cities. Next to that my focus lays on projects that ask for a strong focus on (urban historical) research and a multidisciplinary approach. Next to the mentioned Latin American cases I worked for instance on research with regards to public markets in Zambia with Cityf\u00f6rster Rotterdam. Furthermore I worked on projects in different European countries, from the France (Marseille), to Switzerland (Montana) and Spain (Alicante with Marc Koehler Architects and Architecten Cie.).  ",
